parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch cable can cause the clutch pedal to go all the way to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal goes all the way to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the clutch cable snaps or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck or inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt catches on something and won't extract from the retractor
the seatbelt fails to properly secure the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failure of the seatbelt harness can cause the seatbelt to detach or malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt pops out of its harness during sudden stops or swerves
the passenger is propelled into the dash or other objects
the seatbelt is properly secured but fails to restrain the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause damage to the vehicle, injury to occupants, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of control.
